{"slideshow_credits": null, "snippet": "Restorers painstakingly removed varnish and overpainting from a 15th-century work, after new scanning technology revealed that what lay below was stunning....", "abstract": "Restoration of Ghent Altarpiece, 15th-century biblical masterpiece by Flemish brothers Jan and Hubert Van Eyck, has revealed for first time in hundreds of years individual brush strokes and minute details of original paintings, hidden under layers of over-painting and varnish; restoration has been taking place over four years at Museum of Fine Art in Belgium, using revolutionary scanning technique known as macro-X-ray fluorescence analysis, or MA-XRF.", "section_name": "Science", "print_page": "1", "document_type": "article", "byline": {"person": [{"firstname": "Milan", "role": "reported", "lastname": "SCHREUER", "rank": 1, "organization": ""}], "original": "By MILAN SCHREUER", "contributor": ""}, "web_url": "http://www.nytimes.com/2016/12/19/science/ghent-altarpiece-restoration.html", "lead_paragraph": "Restorers painstakingly removed varnish and overpainting from a 15th-century work, after new scanning technology revealed that what lay below was stunning.", "headline": {"main": "A Master Work, the Ghent Altarpiece, Reawakens Stroke by Stroke", "print_headline": "Uncovering a Master\u2019s Strokes"}, "_id": "5858689995d0e03926076dd5", "word_count": "1658", "multimedia": [{"height": 126, "url": "images/2016/12/20/science/20GHENTJP2/20GHENTJP2-thumbWide.jpg", "legacy": {"wideheight": "126", "wide": "images/2016/12/20/science/20GHENTJP2/20GHENTJP2-thumbWide.jpg", "widewidth": "190"}, "subtype": "wide", "width": 190, "type": "image"}, {"height": 437, "url": "images/2016/12/20/science/20GHENTJP2/20GHENTJP2-articleLarge.jpg", "legacy": {"xlarge": "images/2016/12/20/science/20GHENTJP2/20GHENTJP2-articleLarge.jpg", "xlargewidth": "600", "xlargeheight": "437"}, "subtype": "xlarge", "width": 600, "type": "image"}, {"height": 75, "url": "images/2016/12/20/science/20